definitions: To break up, turn over, or remove earth or other material with a tool or by hand.
To make a hole or channel by removing earth.
To poke or prod someone or something.
examples: They dig for gold in the mountains.
The dog loves to dig holes in the yard.
Archaeologists will dig at the ancient site.
I really dig that new song.
She dug him in the ribs to get his attention.
